---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Platform" description="VScalar Infrastructure Intelligence Platform for cloud migration, operations, enterprise architecture, and zero-trust security.">

  <section class="page-hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">Platform</p>
    <h1>Infrastructure Intelligence Platform</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      VScalar brings together enterprise data, architecture context, deterministic analytics,
      and AI-assisted reasoning to support cloud migration, operations, enterprise architecture,
      and zero-trust security initiatives.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section light">
    <div class="platform-tabs">
      <a href="/cloud-migration">Cloud Migration</a>
      <a href="#operations">Operations</a>
      <a href="#enterprise-architecture">Enterprise Architecture</a>
      <a href="#zero-trust-security">Zero Trust Security</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="platform">
    <h2>Unified Enterprise Data Hub</h2>
    <p>
      At the core of the VScalar platform is a Unified Enterprise Data Hub that brings together
      data from infrastructure, applications, cloud platforms, network telemetry, security systems,
      observability tools, operations platforms, and enterprise architecture sources.
    </p>
    <p>
      This common intelligence layer helps connect fragmented enterprise context and enables
      better assessment, planning, modernization, migration, security analysis, operational
      improvement, and decision support.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section light" id="cloud-migration">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#0284c7;">Cloud Migration</p>
    <h2>Cloud Migration Intelligence</h2>
    <p class="large-text">
      VScalar supports enterprise cloud migration programs by bringing together infrastructure
      inventory, application dependencies, firewall requirements, network context, sizing,
      landing zone design, and AI-assisted decision support into one migration intelligence workflow.
    </p>
    <div class="cards">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Discover</h3>
        <p>Assess infrastructure inventories, technology stacks, ownership, readiness indicators, and migration scope.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Understand</h3>
        <p>Map application dependencies, communication flows, network paths, and security requirements.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Decide</h3>
        <p>Design move groups, migration waves, target patterns, and cloud migration strategies.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Execute</h3>
        <p>Support migration planning, cutover readiness, validation, and decision tracking across the migration lifecycle.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 32px;">
      <a class="btn primary" href="/cloud-migration" style="background:#0f3b63; color:white; text-decoration:none;">Explore Cloud Migration →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="operations" class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#0284c7;">Operations</p>
    <h2>Operations Intelligence</h2>
    <p class="large-text">
      Operations capabilities will focus on operational visibility, observability, incident
      understanding, capacity insights, automation opportunities, and AIOps-enabled improvement.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="enterprise-architecture" class="section light">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#0284c7;">Enterprise Architecture</p>
    <h2>Enterprise Architecture Intelligence</h2>
    <p class="large-text">
      Enterprise Architecture capabilities will focus on assessment, target-state design,
      standards alignment, technology rationalization, transformation roadmaps, and feedback
      loops between architecture, execution, and operations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section id="zero-trust-security" class="section">
    <p class="eyebrow" style="color:#0284c7;">Zero Trust Security</p>
    <h2>Zero Trust Security Intelligence</h2>
    <p class="large-text">
      Zero Trust Security capabilities will focus on segmentation, firewall intelligence,
      connectivity analysis, security posture visibility, policy understanding, and risk-aware
      transformation planning.
    </p>
  </section>

</Base>
